📖 Project Overview
This project is part of the Digital Literacy course and focuses on building essential digital skills required for students in today’s world. It includes learning about digital tools, safe internet practices, professional communication, and cyber awareness.

The project is divided into five tasks, each covering a specific area of digital literacy. All tasks have been completed and organized in this repository.

🧩 Task 1 – Digital Literacy Infographic
In this task, I created a one-page infographic to explain the concept of digital literacy. The infographic covers topics such as safe internet practices, email etiquette, and useful digital tools for students. The design was created using Canva/AI tools with a focus on clarity and visual appeal.

📂 Folder: Task-1 Presentation

💼 Task 2 – Student Digital Portfolio
In this task, I created my profiles on professional platforms to build my digital identity.

GitHub: GitHub Profile
LinkedIn: LinkedIn Profile
Kaggle: Kaggle Profile
These platforms will help me showcase my work, connect with professionals, and improve my technical skills over time.

📂 Folder: Task-2

💻 Task 3 – Coding & Collaboration Platforms
For this task, I explored a coding platform and completed a beginner-level problem to understand programming basics.

I also created a Google Form titled "Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz" to test basic knowledge of digital literacy.

Google Form Link: Digital literacy Google Form
Screenshots of the coding challenge, form, and responses have been added.

📂 Folder: Task-3

✉️ Task 4 – Email Etiquette & Social Media Guidelines
In this task, I learned professional communication by drafting two emails:

Request for assignment extension
Application for internship opportunity
I also created a checklist of Do’s and Don’ts for responsible social media use.

📂 Folder: Task-4

🔐 Task 5 – Cybercrime Awareness
In this task, I studied cybercrime related to UPI fraud and created a case study explaining how such frauds happen.

I also prepared a prevention checklist with safety tips and included official reporting channels.

📂 Folder: Task-5

🎯 Conclusion
This project helped me understand the importance of digital literacy and how to use digital platforms effectively. It improved my awareness about online safety, professional communication, and building a strong digital presence.

📌 Note
All tasks have been completed individually and uploaded in the correct folder structure as required.
